## Finding: Knowledge Audit / Brain-Drain Prevention Has No Coverage

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: feature_walkthrough captures how individual features work. doc_reorganize cleans up document structure. user_documentation builds the help center. None of these perform a systematic knowledge audit to identify tacit knowledge that exists only in the build team's heads and must be externalized before handoff. This is especially critical for: architectural decisions and their rationale (ADRs), environment-specific quirks and gotchas, credentials and access management inventory, and "tribal knowledge" that engineers know but haven't documented. Without a knowledge audit, handoff creates a knowledge vacuum.
### Proposed Resolution: Skill name "knowledge_audit", Phase 6, triggers: "Run knowledge audit for [project]", "Brain-drain prevention checklist", "Knowledge transfer checklist". Scope: Executes a structured interview and documentation process to surface tacit knowledge from the build team, capturing architectural decision records (ADRs), environment gotchas, access inventory, and an explicit "known unknowns" registry before team handoff or offboarding.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 7 (Maintenance) sop_standards, wi_standards, and documentation_standards build on existing documentation — but if foundational knowledge was never captured at handoff, maintenance teams are building on sand. This gap is the leading cause of maintenance failures following successful builds.

