## Finding: Training Material Generation and Onboarding Analytics Are Not Covered

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: user_documentation addresses help centers with onboarding tours (via react-joyride) and in-app contextual help. community_management addresses contributor onboarding for open source projects. But neither skill addresses: generating structured training curricula for new users, measuring onboarding effectiveness through analytics (completion rates, time-to-first-value, drop-off points), or iterating on onboarding based on data. The user_documentation skill notes "feedback metrics are tracked" but this is for help article quality — not the onboarding funnel as a whole.
### Proposed Resolution: Skill name "onboarding_analytics", Phase 6, triggers: "Measure onboarding effectiveness", "Track user onboarding funnel", "Onboarding analytics for [product]". Scope: Instruments the onboarding flow with analytics events (step completion, time-on-step, exit points), creates dashboards for activation metrics (time-to-first-value, 7-day retention by onboarding path), and produces the iteration protocol for improving onboarding based on data.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 5.75 (Beta) product_analytics established analytics infrastructure — but onboarding funnel analytics are a specialized sub-domain that connects the handoff phase directly to long-term user retention, which is a Phase 7 concern.

