## Finding: api_reference Skill Grade — SHALLOW (NestJS-Only, No API Governance)

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: api_reference is graded SHALLOW at the phase level. It is deeply NestJS/Swagger-specific — all 8 parts are NestJS code. Missing coverage: GraphQL schema documentation, gRPC service definitions, REST API documentation for non-NestJS backends (Express, FastAPI, Go), API deprecation management (how to document breaking changes and notify consumers), and API governance (who approves API changes, how breaking changes are communicated, how API contracts are enforced in CI). The SDK generation section covers only TypeScript (Orval, openapi-generator). The API Empathy Checks section is strong but the skill effectively excludes non-NestJS stacks from Phase 6 coverage.
### Proposed Resolution: Expand api_reference to add a "Stack-Agnostic API Documentation" section covering FastAPI auto-docs, Express swagger-jsdoc, and a "API Governance" section covering breaking change policies, deprecation versioning, and consumer notification protocols. This is a depth expansion to the existing skill.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 7 (Maintenance) documentation_standards inherits the API documentation approach. If only NestJS is covered, mixed-stack or polyglot projects have undocumented services at handoff.

