## Finding: community_management Grade — ADEQUATE (Open-Source Only, Missing SaaS/Enterprise Handoff)

### Gap Type: SHALLOW_COVERAGE
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: community_management is graded ADEQUATE for open source projects, SURFACE for proprietary SaaS/enterprise. The skill is explicitly open source oriented (GitHub Issues, contributor ladders, CONTRIBUTING.md, BDFL governance models). For proprietary products handed off to customer success or enterprise account teams, the relevant concepts are: customer success handoff protocols, customer advisory board setup, enterprise onboarding programs, and customer communication channel governance. The current skill sets up the wrong mental model for 60%+ of software handoffs.
