## Finding: Phase 5.75 Beta Feedback Is Not Formally Closed Before Handoff

### Gap Type: MISSING_HANDOFF
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: Phase 5.75 (Beta) includes feedback_system and product_analytics skills. These produce beta feedback data and analytics. Phase 6 (Handoff) has no skill that formally closes the beta feedback loop: reviewing all unresolved beta feedback, triaging it (fix now vs. known issue in backlog vs. won't fix), and producing a "Beta Closure Report" that stakeholders sign off on. The feature_flags skill in Phase 5.75 may have flags still active at handoff. The disaster_recovery and user_documentation skills assume a clean state — but if beta feedback reveals unresolved issues, handoff documentation will be inaccurate or incomplete. There is a structural assumption that beta ends cleanly before Phase 6 begins, but no mechanism to enforce or verify this.
### Proposed Resolution: Skill name "beta_closure", Phase 6 (or Phase 5.75 exit gate), triggers: "Close beta program", "Beta feedback resolution report", "GA readiness from beta". Scope: Produces the formal beta closure report: categorized resolution of all beta feedback, active feature flag inventory with disposition (keep/remove), unresolved issues registered in backlog with priority, and the signed attestation that beta is complete.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 5.75 has no formal exit gate — its work bleeds into Phase 6 without a defined stopping point. Phase 7 inherits the backlog created at this junction.

---

## Finding: Feature Flags Active at Handoff Are Not Inventoried or Transitioned

### Gap Type: MISSING_HANDOFF
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: Phase 5.75 feature_flags establishes a disciplined flag lifecycle: create, deploy, rollout, monitor, remove. However, Phase 6 has no skill that audits which feature flags are still active at the time of handoff and documents their intended state. If a flag is at 50% rollout at handoff time, the incoming maintenance team needs to know: is this flag intended to stay at 50% permanently? Is it supposed to reach 100% during Phase 7? Who owns the flag cleanup? The feature_flags skill says "Monitor for 1 week, then remove flag" — but this presumes the same team is doing both. At a team handoff boundary, flags in intermediate states create operational ambiguity.
### Proposed Resolution: Add to the proposed "operational_readiness_review" skill (Loop 1): a Feature Flag Inventory section that documents every active flag at handoff time, its current rollout percentage, its intended final state, and who owns completing the rollout or cleanup post-handoff.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 7 (Maintenance) receives undefined operational state if flags are in intermediate positions. The flag debt described in feature_flags ("nobody remembers what a flag was for") is most likely to occur precisely at a team handoff boundary.

