## Finding: Rate Limiting Thresholds and Error Boundary Configurations Are Not Documented at Handoff

### Gap Type: MISSING_HANDOFF
### Severity: HIGH
### Evidence: Phase 5.75 (Beta) includes rate_limiting and error_boundaries skills. These establish configuration parameters (rate limits per user/tier, circuit breaker thresholds, error boundary fallback behaviors). Phase 6 has no skill that produces a "Configuration Reference" document — the authoritative record of every tuned parameter, its current value, the rationale for that value (informed by beta traffic), and the threshold at which it should be reconsidered. Without this, Phase 7 maintenance team will not know: what the rate limits are, why they were set that way, or when to adjust them.
