## Finding: No Handoff Ceremony or Communication Plan Exists

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: Working backward from ideal: a successful handoff includes a formal communication event — a handoff meeting, a handoff document distributed to all stakeholders, and a go-live announcement. The current Phase 6 skills produce artifacts (docs, runbooks, API specs) but no communication plan: who gets told about the handoff, in what format, with what information, and at what time? The email_templates skill in Phase 5.75 handles transactional email — but go-live and handoff announcements are a different communication type: stakeholder briefings, press releases for public launches, customer notifications of GA status, internal team announcements.
### Proposed Resolution: Add to the proposed "operational_readiness_review" skill: a "Handoff Communication Plan" section defining: the internal stakeholder announcement, customer-facing GA announcement (if applicable), press/marketing release (if public launch), support team go-live briefing, and the communication timeline coordinating all these outputs.
