## Finding: user_documentation Fails When Product Has No UI (API-Only / Headless Products)

### Gap Type: FAILURE_MODE_UNCOVERED
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: user_documentation is entirely structured around UI-centric products: HelpTooltip components, HelpPanel slide-outs, onboarding tours with CSS selectors, "click the Save button" writing style. For API-only products, developer tools, CLIs, or headless services, the entire skill is inapplicable: there are no UI elements to attach tooltips to, no panels to open, no "click" actions to document. Developer documentation for these products requires: interactive code examples (Runkit, CodeSandbox), SDK reference documentation, CLI command reference, authentication credential management guides, and webhook integration tutorials. These are fundamentally different from the UI-centric help center model.
### Proposed Resolution: Add "Developer-Centric Documentation" section to user_documentation: CLI reference format, SDK getting-started template, webhook integration tutorial template, interactive code example embedding (CodeSandbox/Stackblitz), and developer quickstart guide structure.
### Cross-Phase Impact: API-first products built in Phase 3 without a UI will have no usable documentation at Phase 6 handoff. api_reference covers the technical spec but not the developer experience documentation.

