## Finding: feature_walkthrough Fails Under High Feature Velocity

### Gap Type: FAILURE_MODE_UNCOVERED
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: feature_walkthrough mandates "MANDATORY: Every completed feature MUST have a walkthrough." Under high feature velocity (10+ features shipped in a sprint), this creates a documentation bottleneck: walkthroughs pile up, become outdated before they are completed, and the mandatory requirement becomes impossible to honor without delaying feature releases. The skill provides no prioritization mechanism: which features need walkthroughs most urgently? Are all features equal in walkthrough requirement? How do you triage a 50-feature backlog of missing walkthroughs? The mandatory nature of the skill, without a triage framework, turns into documentation debt in high-velocity contexts.
### Proposed Resolution: Add to feature_walkthrough: a "Walkthrough Triage Matrix" that categorizes features by user-facing impact and complexity to prioritize walkthrough creation, a "Minimal Viable Walkthrough" fast-track template for low-impact features, and a team-velocity-adjusted walkthrough creation schedule.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 7 maintenance will inherit a feature inventory. If walkthroughs were skipped for 30% of features under velocity pressure, Phase 7 documentation_standards work starts with a known gap that was never addressed.

